    "causal_summary": "End-to-end Claude Code hook testing on 2026-04-23 surfaced three findings via two real `claude -p` sessions (b06fd791 enabled, 17e651f5 disable-flag) and five direct hook-script smokes: (A) advisor freshness is stuck in stale-loop because skill-graph-generation.json persists sourceSignature as null, so the source/graph comparison cannot reconcile after a scan; (B) .claude/settings.local.json nests Copilot-schema fields (bash, timeoutSec) alongside Claude-schema fields, producing three hook invocations per UserPromptSubmit where two are expected; (C) no documented multi-turn regression harness means operators pay cache-creation (~41K tokens = ~$0.17) per fresh claude -p test run instead of reusing one session. This Level 2 packet fixes all three: spike freshness internals, persist sourceSignature atomically, normalize settings.local.json to Claude schema only, and add §9 Multi-turn regression harness to the skill-advisor validation playbook.",
